= Energy-Dia Demo Collection

This document introduces all features of the Energy-Dia library step by step. Starting from simple examples, it progresses to more complex chemically meaningful diagrams.

All diagrams can adjust size using `width` and `height` parameters.

*Note: The energy values used in the examples were generated by an LLM or adjusted for visual appeal, so their scientific accuracy is not guaranteed. Please be aware of this.*

== 1. Basics of Atomic Orbital Diagrams

=== 1.1 Simplest Example

A minimal example showing only energy levels.

#ao(
  width: 8,
  height: 6,
  (energy: -10, electrons: 0),
  (energy: -5, electrons: 0),
)

=== 1.2 Basic Example with Electrons

Energy levels containing electrons. Electrons are automatically placed.

#ao(
  width: 8,
  height: 6,
  (energy: -10, electrons: 2),
  (energy: -5, electrons: 1),
)

=== 1.3 With Captions

Display orbital names as captions.

#ao(
  width: 8,
  height: 6,
  (energy: -10, electrons: 2, caption: "1s"),
  (energy: -3, electrons: 2, caption: "2s"),
)

=== 1.4 Representing Degenerate Orbitals

Use degeneracy to represent multiple orbitals at the same energy level.

#ao(
  width: 8,
  height: 6,
  (energy: -10, electrons: 2, caption: "1s"),
  (energy: -5, electrons: 3, degeneracy: 3, caption: "2p"),
)

=== 1.5 Specifying Spin-Up Electrons

You can explicitly specify the number of spin-up electrons with the `up` parameter. If not specified, they are placed alternately automatically.

#ao(
  width: 8,
  height: 6,
  (energy: -10, electrons: 2, caption: "1s"),
  (energy: -5, electrons: 4, degeneracy: 3, up: 3, caption: "2p"),
)

=== 1.6 Displaying Atomic Name

You can display the atomic name with the `name` parameter.

#ao(
  width: 8,
  height: 8,
  name: "C",
  (energy: -10, electrons: 2, caption: "1s"),
  (energy: -3, electrons: 2, caption: "2s"),
  (energy: -1, electrons: 2, degeneracy: 3, caption: "2p"),
)

=== 1.7 Hiding Energy Values

You can hide energy value labels with `exclude_energy: true`.

#ao(
  width: 8,
  height: 8,
  name: "N",
  exclude_energy: true,
  (energy: -14, electrons: 2, caption: "1s"),
  (energy: -3, electrons: 2, caption: "2s"),
  (energy: -1, electrons: 3, degeneracy: 3, up: 3, caption: "2p"),
)

